<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <%- include("../../parts/head") %>
</head>

<body class="d-flex flex-column min-vh-100 bg-wyrd-default">

    <!-- Navbar -->
    <%- include("../../parts/navbar") %>

        <!-- Content -->
        <div class="container min-vh-100 bg-light shadow-lg border-start border-end border-dark-subtle">
            <div class="container-content">
                <!-- Hero Image -->
                <div class="row mb-3">
                    <div class="col">
                        <h3 class="lora-semibold">Society</h3>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <hr>
                <div class="row my-3">
                    <div class="position-relative p-0">
                        <img class="img-fluid w-100 object-fit-cover" src="/img/society.png" />
                        <div class="position-absolute bottom-0 end-0 p-3 w-50">
                            <div class="bg-black p-3 bg-opacity-75 rounded shadow">
                                <span class="lora-medium fst-italic text-light">
                                    The world is held together less by great rulers than by hopsitable neighbors. I
                                    crossed six kingdoms before I found a language I did not know. I crossed none
                                    before I found someone willing to share supper.
                                </span>
                                <div class="lora-semibold text-light text-end mt-2">
                                    Sister Margaret
                                    <br>
                                    <i>The Pilgrim's Path</i>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <hr>
                <div class="row gap-3">
                    <div class="col-md">
                        <p>
                            For most people, life in Aeld is defined less by kings and gods than by the rhythm of the
                            seasons. Farmers tend their fields, merchants travel familiar roads, craftsmen practice
                            trades passed down through generations, and laborers earn their living one day at a time.
                            Most communities are small, close-knit, and largely self-sufficient, relying upon nearby
                            towns for trade and larger cities for goods that cannot be produced locally.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            The Commonwealth's influence is a distant reminder. Daily life is shaped instead by local
                            customs, village elders, magistrates, guilds, temples, and the noble families who govern
                            each region. A traveler may cross several borders in a week's journey, finding familiar
                            languages and customs alongside different laws, currencies, and traditions.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Faith and superstition are woven naturally into everyday life. Shrines stand beside roads,
                            blessings accompany meals and harvests, and travelers often leave offerings before setting
                            out on long journeys. Most people honor several gods over the course of their lives, turning
                            to different patrons as circumstances demand rather than devoting themselves exclusively to
                            a single faith.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

</body>

</html>